# Mintlify Rules - Comprehensive Documentation Guide

## Overview

This guide provides a complete reference for building documentation with Mintlify, including all core components, writing principles, and best practices for creating exceptional technical documentation.

## ✍️ Writing Guidelines
- Use ## as the top-level heading inside content
- Maintain proper heading hierarchy: ##, ###, ####, etc.
- Use inline code for filenames, paths, or code (\example.js``)
- Prefer active voice and short, clear sentences
- Avoid placeholders like foo, bar, or your_api_key
- Use real examples, expected outputs, and comments in code
- Use clear link text — avoid “click here”

